# Group Ratings

## Title Rating [/v1/ratings/{tconst}{?episodes}]

+ Parameters
    + tconst: `tt32459853` (string, required) - IMDb title identifier.
    + episodes (string, optional) - Set to `true` to return the `RatingWithEpisodes` wrapper. Any other value is ignored.

### Get Rating [GET]

Set `episodes=true` to receive the wrapper form with `requestTconst`, optional `rating`, optional `episodesParentTconst`, and `episodes`.

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Rating)

+ Response 404 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 401 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 429 (application/json)
    + Headers

            Retry-After: 1

    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 500 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

## Ratings Bulk [/v1/ratings/bulk{?episodes}]

+ Parameters
    + episodes (string, optional) - Set to `true` to make each result use the `RatingWithEpisodes` wrapper. Any other value is ignored.

### Bulk Get Ratings [POST]

Set `episodes=true` to make each entry in `results` use the `RatingWithEpisodes` wrapper. `missing` still records identifiers that were not found.

The request body must contain only the `identifiers` property. Empty arrays, arrays with more than 250 entries, blank identifiers, malformed JSON, unknown fields, and trailing JSON return `400`.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (BulkRatingsRequest)

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (BulkRatingsResponse)

+ Response 400 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 401 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 429 (application/json)
    + Headers

            Retry-After: 1

    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 500 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

# Group Titles

## Titles Search [/v1/titles/search{?q,types,limit}]

### Search titles [GET]

Search IMDb titles by substring. Results are limited to titles with ratings data (`num_votes > 0`) and ranked by popularity, then start year, then title.

The implementation searches `primary_title` with a case-insensitive substring match. Results are ordered by IMDb vote count descending, then `startYear` descending with unknown years last, then `primaryTitle` ascending.

+ Parameters
    + q: `matrix` (string, required) - Search query. Minimum length 2 characters.
    + types: `movie,tvSeries` (string, optional) - Comma-separated content types to include. Allowed values: `movie`, `tvSeries`. Defaults to both.
    + limit: `10` (number, optional) - Maximum number of results to return. Range 1–50. Default 10.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            X-API-Key: abcdef12.00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff0011223344556677

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Headers

            Cache-Control: public, max-age=60, stale-while-revalidate=300

    + Attributes (TitleSearchResponse)

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    Returned when `q` is shorter than 2 characters, `types` contains an unrecognised value, or `limit` is outside the 1–50 range.

    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 401 (application/json)

    Returned when the `X-API-Key` header is missing or the key fails validation.

    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 429 (application/json)

    Returned when the rate limit for the API key is exceeded.

    + Headers

            Retry-After: 1

    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

+ Response 500 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorEnvelope)

# Group WebSocket

## WebSocket Streaming Search [/v1/ws]

API Blueprint has no native WebSocket grammar. This section documents the `/v1/ws` endpoint using descriptive prose and JSON frame examples.

### Overview

`GET /v1/ws` upgrades an HTTP connection to WebSocket and provides the same title-search capability as `GET /v1/titles/search`, optimised for typeahead. The connection is persistent, the server cancels superseded in-flight queries automatically, and only one search can be in flight per socket at a time.

### Upgrade Request

The client initiates a standard HTTP Upgrade:

```
GET /v1/ws HTTP/1.1
Host: api.nexioapp.org
Upgrade: websocket
Connection: Upgrade
Sec-WebSocket-Key: <base64-nonce>
Sec-WebSocket-Version: 13
X-API-Key: abcdef12.00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff0011223344556677
```

Alternatively use `Authorization: Bearer <key>` in place of `X-API-Key`. Both header forms are identical to the REST authentication model.

### Authentication

Authentication is evaluated on the Upgrade request using the same `X-API-Key` / `Authorization: Bearer` mechanism as every `/v1/*` REST route. A missing or invalid key returns `401` before the upgrade completes. A valid key that has exhausted its rate-limit bucket returns `429`.

**Browser note**: browsers cannot set arbitrary HTTP headers on `new WebSocket(url)`. The recommended workaround is to obtain a short-lived session cookie through the portal's auth flow, or route WebSocket connections through an authorization-proxy that injects the header. Node.js and CLI clients can set `X-API-Key` directly on the Upgrade request.

### Rate Limits

- The Upgrade request counts as one call against the same token-bucket quota used by REST requests. A `429` on the Upgrade means the bucket was empty.
- A maximum of **5 concurrent open WebSocket connections** per API key is permitted. A 6th concurrent connection is rejected with `429` at Upgrade time.
- After a successful Upgrade, individual client messages are **not** metered against the REST quota. Each socket has a local token bucket with a burst of 20 messages and a refill rate of 20 messages per second. Excess `search` messages receive a `{"type":"error","code":"rate_limited","message":"message rate too high"}` frame; the socket remains open.

### Message Protocol

All frames are UTF-8 text frames carrying JSON objects. Binary frames are not used.

#### Client → Server

**search** — submit or replace the current query. Sending a new `search` frame while a previous query is in flight cancels the previous query server-side.

```json
{"type":"search","seq":1,"q":"matrix","types":["movie","tvSeries"]}
```

The WebSocket endpoint always returns at most 10 results. Clients needing larger result sets should use `GET /v1/titles/search`.

| Field    | Type           | Required | Default              | Notes                                                        |
|----------|----------------|----------|----------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| `type`   | string         | yes      | —                    | Must be `"search"`.                                          |
| `seq`    | uint64         | yes      | —                    | Client-supplied monotonic counter. Echoed verbatim in reply. |
| `q`      | string         | yes      | —                    | Search query. Trimmed. Minimum 2 characters.                 |
| `types`  | array[string]  | no       | `["movie","tvSeries"]` | Allowed values: `"movie"`, `"tvSeries"`.                  |

**ping** — keepalive probe. The server replies with a `pong` frame carrying the same `seq`.

```json
{"type":"ping","seq":2}
```

#### Server → Client

**result** — search completed. `results` and `meta` are identical in shape to the REST `/v1/titles/search` response.

```json
{"type":"result","seq":1,"results":[{"tconst":"tt0133093","titleType":"movie","primaryTitle":"The Matrix","startYear":1999}],"meta":{"snapshotId":42,"count":1}}
```

**cancelled** — emitted when a new `search` frame arrived before the previous query finished. `seq` echoes the cancelled query's sequence number.

```json
{"type":"cancelled","seq":1}
```

**error** — the request was rejected or a server fault occurred. `seq` echoes the triggering message's sequence number.

```json
{"type":"error","seq":1,"code":"invalid_request","message":"q must be at least 2 characters"}
```

```json
{"type":"error","seq":0,"code":"invalid_request","message":"invalid JSON"}
```

```json
{"type":"error","seq":1,"code":"invalid_request","message":"unknown message type"}
```

| `code`             | Meaning                                                                        |
|--------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `invalid_request`  | Invalid JSON, unknown message type, `q` too short, or unknown `types` value.   |
| `rate_limited`     | Local per-socket message-rate ceiling exceeded. Socket stays open.             |
| `internal_error`   | Unexpected server fault while processing a search.                             |

**pong** — reply to a `ping`. `seq` echoes the ping's sequence number.

```json
{"type":"pong","seq":2}
```

### In-Flight Query Semantics

Only one `search` can be in flight per socket at a time. When the client sends a second `search` before the first has resolved:

1. The server cancels the first query.
2. The server emits `{"type":"cancelled","seq":<prior-seq>}`.
3. The server begins processing the new query and eventually emits `{"type":"result","seq":<new-seq>,...}`.

### WebSocket Close Codes

| Code   | Meaning                                                                          |
|--------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `1000` | Normal closure. The read loop closes with normal closure when the connection ends. |
| `1001` | Going away. The server uses this when the protocol ping keepalive times out.      |

# Data Structures

## HealthResponse (object)
+ status: ok (string, required)

## ReadinessResponse (object)
+ status: ready (string, required)

## ErrorEnvelope (object)
+ error (ErrorDetails, required)

## ErrorDetails (object)
+ code: invalid_request (string, required)
+ message: request parameters are invalid (string, required)

## SnapshotsResponse (object)
+ items (array[Snapshot], required)

## Stats (object)
+ ratings: 1600000 (number, required)
+ episodes: 6200000 (number, required)
+ snapshots: 12 (number, required)

## Snapshot (object)
+ id: 1 (number, required)
+ dataset: title.ratings.tsv.gz (string, required)
+ status: active (string, required)
+ syncMode: delta (string, optional)
+ datasetVersion: 2026-03-22 (string, optional)
+ importedAt: 2026-03-22T18:02:11Z (string, required)
+ sourceUpdatedAt: 2026-03-22T12:34:20Z (string, optional)
+ sourceETag: W/"etag-value" (string, optional)
+ isActive: true (boolean, required)
+ ratingCount: 1600000 (number, required)
+ episodeCount: 6200000 (number, required)
+ notes: Imported successfully. (string, optional)
+ sourceUrl: https://datasets.imdbws.com/title.ratings.tsv.gz (string, optional)
+ completedAt: 2026-03-22T18:05:00Z (string, optional)

## Rating (object)
+ tconst: tt32459853 (string, required)
+ averageRating: 7.8 (number, required)
+ numVotes: 1500 (number, required)

## EpisodeRating (object)
+ tconst: tt32459853 (string, required)
+ parentTconst: tt27444205 (string, required)
+ seasonNumber: 1 (number, optional)
+ episodeNumber: 2 (number, optional)
+ averageRating: 7.8 (number, required)
+ numVotes: 1500 (number, required)

## RatingWithEpisodes (object)
+ requestTconst: tt27444205 (string, required)
+ rating (Rating, optional)
+ episodesParentTconst: tt27444205 (string, optional)
+ episodes (array[EpisodeRating], required)

## BulkRatingsRequest (object)
+ identifiers (array[string], required) - One to 250 non-blank IMDb title identifiers. Values are trimmed before lookup.
    + tt32459853
    + tt0944947

## BulkRatingsResponse (object)
+ results (array[Rating], required)
+ missing (array[string], required)

## BulkRatingsWithEpisodesResponse (object)
+ results (array[RatingWithEpisodes], required)
+ missing (array[string], required)

## TitleSearchResponse (object)
+ results (array[TitleSearchResult], required)
+ meta (TitleSearchMeta, required)

## TitleSearchResult (object)
+ tconst: tt0133093 (string, required)
+ titleType: movie (string, required) - `movie` or `tvSeries`.
+ primaryTitle: The Matrix (string, required)
+ startYear: 1999 (number, optional) - Omitted when the title has no known start year.

## TitleSearchMeta (object)
+ snapshotId: 42 (number, required)
+ count: 1 (number, required)
